body:
# Bug report

**What is the current behavior?**

Values outside of any HMR lifecycle callbacks have their values correctly defined, but calls within HMR callbacks don't get them.

**If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce.**

An example - let's say we use `DefinePlugin` and provide a value called `__test__` with a value of `true`:

```js
// This will successfully print out the value of `__test__`
console.log(__test__);

if (module.hot) {
  module.hot.accept(() => {
    // This call will fail with a `ReferenceError`
    console.log(__test__);
  });
}
```

Running `webpack` will yield:

```js
console.log(true);

if (module.hot) {
  module.hot.accept(() => {
    console.log(__test__);
  });
}
```

**What is the expected behavior?**

In `webpack@4`, values are correctly injected into the HMR callbacks:

```js
console.log(true);

if (module.hot) {
  module.hot.accept(() => {
    console.log(true);
  });
}
```

I'm not sure if this is the intended behaviour - but `ProvidePlugin` does work in HMR callbacks. I would assume the two plugins should somewhat align, either both works or both don't?

**Other relevant information:**
webpack version:  5.0.0-beta.18
Node.js version:  14.4.0
Operating System: macOS 10.15.5
Additional tools: None
